news.title: Now, Rs 4 lakh aid for death at construction site: Haryana CM
news.para: “The financial assistance of Rs 2.5 lakh given to a family in case of death of a construction worker at the workplace will be raised to Rs 4 lakh. Similarly, the financial assistance given to a worker in case of disability due to an accident at the workplace will also be doubled,” the CM said.

news.title: Interest from co-operative bank exempt for housing societies in Mumbai: ITAT
news.para: Co-operative housing societies park their surplus funds with other co-operative entities (that is, banks) and claim tax exemption for the interest under Section 80P of the I-T Act.

news.title: Maharashtra: Citizens set to get ULPIN & property cards from September 19
news.para: The state settlement commissioner, N K Sudhanshu said the existing 3 crore documents, comprising 2.6 crore 7/12 extracts and 70 lakh property cards, had been issued the Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN) and revenue department officials were checking them.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body's land auction draws poor response
news.para: The VMRDA had invited applications for sale of 10 land pockets located in different areas of Visakhapatnam and Anakapalli districts. Measuring about 24 acres, auctions of these lands were supposed to be conducted on September 12 and 15.

news.title: In Noida, you can now sign rent agreement online
news.para: Persons wishing to engage in a rental transaction will now only need to register on a portal, pay relevant fees and have their lease deed registered within a matter of minutes.

news.title: Lucknow: No map approval required for building on plot less than 1,076 sq ft
news.para: ​​The circular comes in the wake of substantial number of queries being received by the LDA regarding approval of maps.

news.title: Noida: NMRC officials meet RWAs on Botanical Garden-Sector 142 route
news.para: Ritu Maheshwari, the NMRC managing director, said that the meeting with representatives of different residents' welfare associations, villagers and other stakeholders aimed at consultation on the proposed metro route to obtain the maximum benefits.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: CRDA cuts sale price of plots to woo buyers
news.para: The CRDA set the basic price for various categories of plots depending on the prevailing market prices, and the potential buyers can bid over and above the basic price by participating in e-auction process.

news.title: Gujarat: New rules, GST rate make brick makers see red
news.para: The Gujarat Brick Manufacturers Federation has resolved to not start production in the new season from October, to protest the new notification as well as the increase in GST rates.

news.title: Brihanmumbai municipal corporation collections from builders set to crash
news.para: In 2021, the BMC offered a 50% discount on premium payments for 13 months from January 2021 till January 31, 2022 in a bid to revive business after the pandemic.

news.title: Delhi's property owners in a fix over circle rate, market value mismatch
news.para: Experts believe the solution for both the cases lies in either rationalising the circle rates or reclassification of colonies as per the prevailing trends and facilities.

news.title: AAI eyes 300 acres to increase handling capacity of Chennai airport
news.para: The decision was made after AAI Chairman Sanjeev Kumar and the board evaluated the new terminal's construction and talked about the need for more airport land so that more facilities such as parking lots and parallel taxiways could be built to boost passenger capacity to 55 million per year.

news.title: Punjab vigilance bureau files FIR against officials for preparing fabricated reports in LIT scam
news.para: The Vigilance Bureau (VB) said during the investigation of the case, it has been found that officials of the LIT with corrupt practices and in connivance with others, had allotted residential plots to unauthorised persons under the LDP scheme.

news.title: Illegal structures in 'forest' areas of four villages in Faridabad to be demolished
news.para: The Haryana forest department this week asked the Faridabad administration to list all illegal structures in 'forest' areas within the next 15 days.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board's fresh pitch for freehold conversion of commercial units
news.para: Even as city residents await a conversion policy for their leasehold commercial properties, the UT administration’s own agency, Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB), is finding it hard to get the UT nod for conversion of its own leasehold properties.
